data.title: Go West (1940 film)
data.text:
Go West is a 1940 film about the men who help young man, trying to settle an old family feud so he can marry the girl he loves.

Directed by Edward Buzzell. Written by Irving Brecher.

JUMP INTO YOUR BOOTS AND SADDLES...IT'S ROUND-UP TIME IN THE WILD AND WOOLY WEST! (taglines)

S. Quentin Quale

[edit]

Any resemblance between these two characters and living persons is purely accidental!

I was going to thrash them within an inch of their lives, but I didn't have a tape measure.

Lulubelle, it's you! I didn't recognize you standing up.

Time wounds all heels.

There's something corrupt going on around my pants but I just can't seem to locate it.

I give you my solemn word as an embezzler, I'll be back in ten minutes.

You must fan the flames of love with the bellows of indifference.

I'm not in business for love, you know. I was in love once and I got the business.

I'm not drunk, but, what's the ceiling doing on the floor?

Joseph Panello

[edit]

Rusty, I no like-a the West. All-a the people do is kill each other. I like-a the West better if it was in the East. Let's get outta here.

[to Quale] You said you was an embezzler, but, you no fool me. I knew you was a crook!

Dialogue

[edit]

Indian: White man talk too much. Make Chief heap mad.

S. Quentin Quale: White man, red man's friend. White man want to make friends with red brother.

Joseph Panello: And sister, too.

S. Quentin Quale: There's only one law in the west: the law of blood and bullets. It's either shoot or be shot. What are we gonna do?

Joseph Panello: Sue'em!

Joseph Panello: My father-a shot the Indians in eighteen forty-two

S. Quentin Quale: Oh, he should-a shot the stork-a, when the stork-a brought-a you.

S. Quentin Quale: Are you insinuating that the white man is not the Indian's friend? Ha! Who swindled you out of Manhattan Island for 24 dollars?

Joseph Panello: White man.

S. Quentin Quale: Who turned you into wood and stood you in front of a cigar store?

Joseph Panello: White man.

S. Quentin Quale: Who put your head on a nickel and then took the nickel away?

Joseph Panello: Slot machine.

S. Quentin Quale: Members of the tribe - I rest my case.

S. Quentin Quale: This is the last hat of it's kind. The beaver's have stopped making them. They're all out playing football. Ten dollars.

Joseph Panello: Well, he's a poor boy. He'll give you a dollar. Will you take it?

S. Quentin Quale: Well, I'll take it but I'm only making a buck on it.

S. Quentin Quale: What did he say?

Joseph Panello: He said, first they're going to give us a fair trial, then they kill us.

Taglines

[edit]

JUMP INTO YOUR BOOTS AND SADDLES...IT'S ROUND-UP TIME IN THE WILD AND WOOLY WEST!

The Looniest, Tuniest Musical Gag-And-Gal Show Since "A Night At The Opera"

Rip-Roaring With Laughs, Girls, Songs!
